Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第七集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.66,0:02:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,為了要說清楚彼得森的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can't really tell Pat Patterson's story
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.60,0:02:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,必須要從很久很久以前地球誕生前說起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without going all the way back to the time long before the earth our home, was built,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,那時星星剛剛產生它的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the stars brought forth its substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.47,0:02:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Iron
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來了行星的熾熱內核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the planet's molten core.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,氧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.04,0:03:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來了岩石 水和空氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the rocks and the water and the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來了鑽石和生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For diamonds. And life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆星誕生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A star is born,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,最初的幾百萬年裏 一切還算順利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For the first few million years, things ran smoothly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,塵土顆粒滾雪球般的逐漸變成更大的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as dust grains snowballed into progressively larger objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,直到這個物體大到一定程度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But once these objects grew massive enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.77,0:03:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,有了足夠的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to have sufficient gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.71,0:04:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,它們開始相互吸引 從而軌道相交相撞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they began pulling each other into crossing orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們的世界最初的模樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is how our world looked when it was new.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,地球表面沒有地方可以倖免於難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No part of the earth's surface could survive intact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,一直到現在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from that time to the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.39,0:04:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,既然地球的幼年記錄都不復存在了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, with all its birth and early childhood records erased,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.06,0:04:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我們怎麼才能確定地球真正的年紀呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how could we ever hope to know with any certainty the true age of our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這是個自古以來的謎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}People have been wondering about this since antiquity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.36,0:04:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,1650年 愛爾蘭大主教詹姆斯·烏捨爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1650 archbishop James Ussher of Ireland
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,得出一個貌似正確的結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}made a calculation that seemed to settle the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就和當時大多數人一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like almost everyone else of his time and his world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他的根據是聖經的造物論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he accepted the biblical account of creation as authoritative.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但是聖經裏也沒有提到具體的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the Bible does not give exact years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,於是烏捨爾在舊約中尋找一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so Ussher searched for an event in the Old Testament
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.81,0:05:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,與已知歷史事件相吻合的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that corresponded to a known historical date.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,他在列王記下卷中發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He found it in the second book of kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,巴比倫統治者尼布甲尼撒二世死於公元前562年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the death of the Babylonian ruler Nebuchadnezzar in 562 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.31,0:05:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,烏捨爾將世代的先知和族長加起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Usher added up the generations of the prophets and the Patriarchs,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,舊約中的139個族譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the 139 "Begats" of the Old Testament,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,從亞當一直到尼布甲尼撒二世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between Adam and the time of Nebuchadnezzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,這個世界誕生於10月22號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the world began on October 22
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.76,0:05:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,公元前4004年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the year 4004 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,下午六點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At 6:00 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.16,0:05:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,星期六\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.16,0:05:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,烏捨爾大主教制定的年表在當時的西方被奉為真理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Archbishop Ussher's chronology was taken as gospel in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.83,0:05:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我們通過另一種途徑瞭解地球的年紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until we turned to another book to find the age of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,通過研究岩石本身的記錄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the one that was written in the rocks themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,科羅拉多大峽谷中大多數的岩層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the rock layers in the walls of the Grand Canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.27,0:05:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,都屬於沉積岩 由許多細小的顆粒堆積而成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are made of sediments, deposited as fine grains
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,這些沉積岩形成的時候 這裏還是海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a time when this part of the world was a sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,年復一年 沉積物被不斷增加的新沉積物壓縮成了岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over eons, the sediments were compressed into rock under the weight of succeeding layers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,最下面的就是最古老的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the oldest ones at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.02,0:06:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,隨便選一層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pick a layer, any layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那個怎麼樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.26,0:06:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以前 這裏水並不深\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once upon a time, there must have been shallow water here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在前寒武紀時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back in the Precambrian period,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,大約10億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about a billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,那時只有一種生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there was only one kind of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,這些藍綠色的細菌忙著收穫陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These blue-green bacteria were busy harvesting sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,從而產生氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and making oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.81,0:07:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,對他們來說那只是廢氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For them, it was just a waste product,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,但對於後來的動物 包括我們來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but for the animals who evolved later, including us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那是孕育生命的呼吸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it was the breath of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,另選一層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay. Pick another layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那個怎麼樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.38,0:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這層被稱為光明天使頁岩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This layer is known as the bright angel shale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,形成於5.3億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It formed about 530 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這些足跡屬於2.6億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These tracks were left 260 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你想知道地球的年紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So you want to know the age of the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.49,0:07:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,只要瞭解形成每一層所需的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just figure out how long it took to deposit each layer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要把族譜加起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and then, instead of counting the "Begats,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.90,0:07:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,把這些層次加起來就夠了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}add up all the layers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.73,0:07:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,很簡單吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Easy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一個問題 我們是根據觀察這個過程得出的結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just one problem, We know from observing this process,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.17,0:07:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它還在持續\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because it still happens today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在海洋中 在湖泊中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in oceans and lakes around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,沉積層的形成時間長度各不相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That sediments can be laid down at widely different rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,通常都是非常的緩慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It usually happens very slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,大約1000年才有1英尺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}say a foot of sediment per 1,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.84,0:07:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果發生了罕見的大洪災\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But when the's a rare catastrophic flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:07:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,速度就會快很多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it can happen much faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,幾天就已經有1英尺了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as much as a foot in just a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.35,0:08:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,許多地質學家嘗試用這種方式來計算地球的年紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many geologists tried this method to calculate the age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他們勘探了大峽谷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They used the Grand Canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.69,0:08:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,還有地球上其他的沉積層區域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and other sedimentary sequences around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.09,0:08:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他們的結論差異卻無法統一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But their answers ranged too widely to be of much use,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,差異範圍從300萬年到150億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}anywhere between three million years and 15 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,這個方法還有其他的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And there were other problems with this method:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,即使最下層的岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even the deepest layers of rock
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,也不是地球上最古老的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are not the oldest things on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.17,0:08:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,因為即使岩石也不能從地球最初所受的災難中倖存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why? Because not even rocks could survive the earth's violent infancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,而太空 那又是另一回事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In space it's another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,地球誕生時留下了任何的紀念品嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Are there any mementos from when the earth was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,有可以證明真實年齡的物體嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}objects that could possibly tell us its true age?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道一個地方 可以找到當年太陽系形成時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know a place where the unused bricks and mortar left over
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,殘留的遺跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the creation of our solar system can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它們存在於木星和火星的軌道間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It lies between the orbits of Jupiter and Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,這些是產生地球的原料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here is the stuff of the newborn earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它們在冰冷的太空中飄蕩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}adrift in cold storage, unchanged
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.23,0:09:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,從未改變過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ever since that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.03,0:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,100萬年左右之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A million or so years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.03,0:09:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆大的小行星恰巧擊撞了一顆較小的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a large asteroid happened to jostle a much smaller one,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.76,0:09:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,將它推到一個新的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sending it on a new trajectory,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它的運動軌跡在大約5萬年前的一個夜晚終結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a collision course that ended one night some 50,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,它從天空劃過打破了大峽谷的平靜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It must have shattered the peace of the Grand Canyon as it sailed overhead...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.65,0:10:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,撞擊形成這個大坑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to blast out this crater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即大峽谷所在的州
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在後來這裏被稱為 亞利桑那\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in what would one day be known as Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆鐵質小行星的碎片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fragments of the iron asteroid that made this crater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.67,0:10:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,被完整的保留了下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have survived intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們知道這塊鐵的形成時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we just knew how long ago that iron was forged,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就能知道太陽系的年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'd know the age of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,也包括地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Including the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.47,0:10:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼才能知道呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But how could we know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.34,0:10:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,挑塊石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pick a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,隨便一塊石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Any rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:10:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,這個怎麼樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How about that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊石頭中的某些原子可能具有放射性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some atoms in this rock could be radioactive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,它們自然地發生衰變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which means they spontaneously disintegrate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.15,0:11:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,從而變成其他元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and become other elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,鈾原子首先變成釷原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A uranium atom first becomes a thorium atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.62,0:11:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,平均而言 耗時十幾億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On average, it takes a few billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,釷很不穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The thorium is much more unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不到一個月的時間就能變成鏷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In less than a month it turns into protactinium.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,一分鐘後 鏷又變成了其他元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A minute later, protactinium becomes something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,又經過10次的核轉變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The atom undergoes ten more nuclear transmutations...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,來到衰變鏈的最後一環\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until it reaches the last stop on the decay chain:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}衰變鏈指的是放射性衰變過程中成鏈產生的一系列衰變產物
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,一個穩定的鉛原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A stable atom of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.47,0:11:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛將不再發生變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And lead it will remain... For eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.30,0:11:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,20世紀有個巨大的成就  在幾十年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the 20th century there was a huge effort, lasting decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.67,0:11:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,測量每種放射性元素轉變成另一種元素所用的時間後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to measure the time it takes for each radioactive element to transmute into another element.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,物理學家發現每個不穩定元素的原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Physicists discovered that the atoms of each unstable element
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.51,0:11:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,衰變比率是恆定的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}decay at a constant rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:12:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,原子的原子核就像一座聖殿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nucleus of an atom is a kind of sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,無視震動和環境的改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}immune to the shocks and upheavals of its environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,用錘子砸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hit it with a hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.19,0:12:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在油裏炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Boil it in oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,氣化它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vaporize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,原子鐘走的不緊不慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nuclear clock goes on ticking,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.23,0:12:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,每一跳的時間都絕對標準\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}keeping an absolute standard of time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不論日月星辰的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that does not look to the sun and the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,要瞭解地球真實的年齡 沒有比測量鈾原子更好的辦法了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What better way to find the true age of the earth than with the uranium atom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.87,0:12:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,只要知道岩石中鈾衰變成鉛的比率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you knew what fraction of the uranium in a rock had turned into lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,就可以計算出岩石存在了多久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you could calculate how much time had passed since the rock was formed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.21,0:12:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但有個問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,形成之初的那些岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rocks in the earth that were present when it was formed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.48,0:12:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,都已不復存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.58,0:12:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,或被壓碎了 或被融化了 或者被重塑了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've all been crushed, melted, remade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.72,0:13:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有個辦法可以計算出鉛的最初數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is a way to calculate the amount of lead that was present from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.32,0:13:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,天賜的禮物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a gift from the heavens:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,隕石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Meteorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊碎片來自造成這個大坑的隕石 很理想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This one... A fragment of the one that made this giant crater... Was ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊隕石中鉛的含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The amount of lead deep inside this meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,與地球形成時的完全一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is exactly the same as when earth formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.93,0:13:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,既然知道了鈾衰變的固定比率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since you know the constant rate of uranium decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,就可以知道這塊隕石的年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that should give you the age of the meteorite,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,和地球的年齡一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which was made at the same time as the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.06,0:13:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,只要測量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All you had to do was measure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,隕石中的鉛就行了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the amount of lead in meteorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,很簡單吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Easy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.91,0:13:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一位在芝加哥大學名叫哈理森·布朗的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A scientist named Harrison Brown at the University of Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,1947年首次掌握了這個方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}first understood this in 1947.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他選擇了一位研究生來實際操作 克萊爾·彼得森\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He chose a young graduate student, Clair Patterson, to do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,當時彼得森怎麼也不會想到這個作業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson couldn't possibly know how this assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,會改變他的一生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would alter the course of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,還有這個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.09,0:14:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,表面上只是單純的科學研究\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What seemed like pure scientific research
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,結果卻不簡單\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}turned out to be so much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.29,0:14:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,克萊爾·彼得森 愛荷華州一位郵遞員的兒子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Clair Patterson, son of a letter carrier from Iowa,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,天性叛逆 學校表現一般\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was rebellious by nature and not very good in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但他卻是天生的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But he was a natural born scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.67,0:14:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,一位名叫哈里森·布朗的地質學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A geologist named Harrison Brown
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.10,0:15:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,交給彼得森一項看似簡單的科學作業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gave Patterson what seemed like a straightforward scientific assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,首先 派特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}First off, Pat...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.24,0:15:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你不介意我叫你派特吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You mind if I call you Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你不是地質學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, I know you're no geologist...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.11,0:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,很可能還分不清長石和花崗岩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}probably couldn't tell granite from feldspar...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.78,0:15:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但我聽說你使用質譜儀很在行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but I hear you really know your way around a mass spectrometer, Pat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 結婚了嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Good. You married, Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.29,0:15:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,結了 她叫勞瑞 也是研究化學的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yeah, Laurie. Yeah, she-she's a chemist, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們曾在橡樹嶺一起為曼哈頓計劃工作過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, we worked on the Manhattan Project together,at Oak Ridge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}第二次世界大戰期間研發與製造原子彈的一項大型軍事工程
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.16,0:15:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,好 很好 首先你要瞭解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Good. Okay, well, first thing you need to know:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,這些被稱為鋯石的小晶體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are these tiny crystals called zircons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.89,0:15:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,非常小 針尖大小 結構緊密 堅硬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Real small, size of a pinhead, tight as a drum and tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,穩定性極高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing gets in or out of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.50,0:15:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十億年如一日\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And I'm talking for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我們通過對包含它們的岩石年份測定 得知了它們的年份\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We know how old these grains are because we've already dated the rocks they came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,每個鋯石只含有百萬分之幾的鈾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each little zircon has only a few parts per million
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.30,0:15:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,而這些鈾又進一步衰變為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of uranium inside, and that uranium is decaying
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.57,0:15:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,更少量的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to even tinier amounts of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,只要測量出鉛的含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, you figure out how to measure that lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.74,0:15:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,就能知道隕石的年代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and you'll know how to do it for a meteorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.44,0:15:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你能做到嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You think you can do that, Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.64,0:16:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,可以 應該沒問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yeah. Yeah, I... I don't see why not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.25,0:16:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 如果你做到了 你就是第一個知道地球年齡的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Good, because when you do, you'll be the first man to know the age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.78,0:16:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你就出名了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And you'll be famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,很簡單的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And you'll see: It'll be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.29,0:16:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,易如反掌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Duck soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,當彼得森在測量鋯石微粒中的微量鉛時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}While Patterson tried to measure the trace amounts of lead in the zircon grains
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.50,0:16:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,另外一位名叫喬治迪爾頓的研究生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another grad student, George Tilton,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.87,0:16:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,也在測定鋯石中的鈾含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was measuring the amount of uranium in the same grains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森只要對鉛含量做等精度測量就可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All Patterson had to do was measure the amount of lead with equal accuracy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即保持測量條件不變
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.51,0:16:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,交給你了 派特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She's all yours, Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.88,0:16:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,測了6次 結果相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Measured it six times. Same result:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:16:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,百萬分之3.2\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}3.2 parts per million.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.64,0:16:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 喬治 謝啦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yeah, nice going, George, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,迪爾頓的結果每次都是一樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tilton's results were always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.95,0:17:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,但是彼得森測量相同微粒的鉛含量的結果卻差別很大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Patterson's results on the lead content of the same grains were wildly inconsistent
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.02,0:17:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,沒道理啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This made no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能是因為以前含鉛實驗污染了實驗室嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Could the lab have been contaminated by previous experiments with lead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.23,0:17:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,或許是自然界中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it was the naturally high amounts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.23,0:17:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,高含量的鉛影響了實驗結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of lead in the environment that were messing up his results.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.17,0:17:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森用盡了辦法清除實驗室的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson did everything he could to cleanse the lab of any lead
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.44,0:17:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,數月後
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.87,0:18:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛含量還是超出了100倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was still 100 times too much lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.54,0:18:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他已經花費了2年多的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had been at it for more than two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,易如反掌個鬼啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Duck soup, my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.21,0:18:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}禁止入內
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.38,0:18:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森意識到他必須用酸來煮容器和工具\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson realized he would have to boil his containers and tools in acid
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.71,0:18:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,並且提純化學原料 以進一步的降低實驗室中的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and purify all his chemicals to further reduce the lead in his lab
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不要啊 噢 我是新來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hey, you... Oh, I... No! I'm new here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,廁所在哪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, where's the men's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.65,0:18:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,見鬼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ugh damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.39,0:18:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不論彼得森怎樣擦洗消毒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All of Patterson's obsessive scouring and sterilizing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.06,0:18:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,都沒能夠解決問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had still not solved the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他必須從頭開始設計建造他自己的實驗室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He would need to design his own lab and build it from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,哈里森布朗轉去位於帕薩迪納的加州理工學院時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The opportunity arose when Harrison Brown moved
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.13,0:18:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,機會出現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the California Institute of Technology in Pasadena
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他邀請彼得森同行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and invited Patterson to join him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.00,0:18:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}加州理工學院
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.50,0:18:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}禁止入內
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}警告 無菌環境
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.00,0:19:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}限制區域 只許實驗人員進入
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.04,0:19:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 湯姆 可以了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, Tom, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.51,0:19:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在可以進去了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We can move through the interlock, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森在這個項目上已經花費了6年時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson had now been at it for six years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,堅持不懈的找到並消滅了許多對儀器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}doggedly tracking down and eliminating the many sources of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.25,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,造成影響的鉛的源頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that were compromising his instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他建造了世界上第一個超級潔淨室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had built the world's first ultra-clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.89,0:19:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他終於可以測量出岩石中鉛的確切含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was finally able to measure how much lead was actually in the rock
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,岩石的年代已經確定了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One whose age had already been established.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.06,0:19:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森終於可以利用這塊鐵隕石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, at last, Patterson was ready to tackle the iron meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.16,0:19:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,找出地球的年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to find the true age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.06,0:19:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他將隕石樣本帶到阿貢國家實驗室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He brought his meteorite specimen back to the Argonne National Laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.43,0:19:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏 世界上最精確的質譜儀剛剛投入使用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where the world's most accurate mass spectrometer had just become operational
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.97,0:19:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,博士 就不能等到明天嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Doc, this can't wait till tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.65,0:20:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 小傢伙 我們要把你氣化了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, little buddy, we're gonna have to vaporize you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.14,0:20:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,質譜儀利用磁場將樣本中的元素分離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A mass spectrometer uses magnets to separate the elements contained in a sample
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,從而使得各種元素可以被量化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that the amounts of each element can be quantified.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.31,0:20:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是解開地球真實年齡之謎的最後一環\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This would provide the last missing piece in the puzzle of the earth's true age
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.72,0:20:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 我要把你離子化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now I'm gonna ionize you, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.49,0:20:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有聽上去那麼可怕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sounds worse than it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.65,0:20:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,小夥伴們很親密呦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's an electron between friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,杜絕了樣本被外界的鉛污染後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Having isolated the sample from any outside lead contamination,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.19,0:21:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森終於可以測量樣本中的鉛和鈾的含量了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson was, at last, ready to measure the amount of lead and uranium in the sample
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,並且測定它形成的年代了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and calculate how many years before it had formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的真實年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The true age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.97,0:21:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝所有做出過貢獻的科學家們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thank you to all the scientists who came before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝地質學家們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thank you, geologists.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝查爾斯·萊爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thank you, Charles Lyell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}著名地質學家 均變說的重要論述者
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝邁克爾·法拉第\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thank you, Michael Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}發現電磁感應
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.14,0:21:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,約瑟夫·湯姆森\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}J.J. Thomson.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.14,0:21:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}發現電子
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,歐內斯特·盧瑟福\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ernest Rutherford.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}核物理之父
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,感謝哈里森·布朗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thank you, Harrison Brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}研究如何分開鈽和鈾
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.53,0:22:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的年齡是45億歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world is four and a half billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我們成功了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,媽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,媽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.11,0:22:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森想最先把這個困擾他多年的謎團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson wanted his mother to be the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.43,0:22:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,與他的母親分享\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to know what he had struggled for so many years to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的真實年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The true age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.58,0:22:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,這項發現為他帶來什麼獎勵嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His reward for this discovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.55,0:22:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,天大的麻煩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A world of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.65,0:22:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他當時並不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He didn't know it, but he was on a collision course
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.03,0:22:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他妨礙了某些世界上最有權力的人的利益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with some of the most powerful people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.52,0:23:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,對於古羅馬人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To the ancient Romans,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,雄偉的土星並不是一個地點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the majestic ringed planet Saturn was not a real place,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其單詞也有農神的意思
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.92,0:23:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,也不是星球 而是天神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not a world, but a God King,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,天地結合的結晶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a son of the marriage of heaven and earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.76,0:23:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the God of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這些立柱都是羅馬廣場上最古老神廟的遺跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These columns are all that remain of this oldest temple in the Roman forum
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.87,0:23:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,最早是在2500年前供奉農神\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}first consecrated to Saturn 2,500 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.43,0:23:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,後來用做羅馬的金庫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It also served as Rome's treasury
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,也做過計量局\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its bureau of weights and measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.00,0:23:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,今天是古羅馬的農神節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tonight is Saturnalia,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.04,0:24:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,向農神表示敬意的12月狂歡節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the wild december holiday in Saturn's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.44,0:24:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,日常生活行為徹底顛倒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And everyday life will be turned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,主人為奴僕服務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The masters will serve the slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,停止一切戰爭和死刑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no wars or executions will be allowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.68,0:24:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,人們相互給予禮物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and gifts will be exchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.58,0:24:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A couple of hundred years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.28,0:24:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,當早年間的牧師們想要吸引更多教徒時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the early church fathers look for a way to attract more pagans,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他們把農神節變成了聖誕節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they'll decide to turn Saturnalia into Christmas,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.25,0:24:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,給這個冬季的節日賦予了新的意義\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making it the latest in a long line of winter solstice holidays to be re-purposed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,在農神節的夜晚這個高聳的農神神像看上去好像是這個樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This towering statue of Saturn may have look something like this on the night of saturnalia
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.93,0:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在古羅馬 他還有更陰暗的一面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in ancient Rome, this God had another, darker side.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.80,0:24:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,農神是一個冷酷的憤懣的行動遲緩的食屍鬼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That other Saturn is a cold and sullen, sluggish ghoul,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.90,0:24:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,動不動就亂發脾氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}given to irrational bouts of rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.97,0:24:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她對他父親的罪行難以言喻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He committed an unspeakable act of violence against his father,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.07,0:24:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至吞噬了自己的孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and devoured his own children.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.61,0:25:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在所有古人能用肉眼看見的行星中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of all the planets visible to the unaided eyes of the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.81,0:25:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,土星的速度是最慢的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Saturn is the slowest,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.28,0:25:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這也就是古人用鉛神的名字為他命名的原因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which could explain why it's named after the God of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.12,0:25:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,不可否認的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's no denying
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.82,0:25:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,農神性格的陰暗面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the more negative aspects of Saturn's personality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.92,0:25:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,其實反映的是古代人們對於鉛中毒的認識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}reflect the age-old knowledge of the symptoms of lead poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.92,0:25:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,有意思的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Funny thing about the Romans.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.42,0:25:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管他們知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even though they knew
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.06,0:25:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,接觸鉛會使人中毒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that contact with lead inevitably poisoned people,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,造成不育還有發狂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rendered them sterile and drove them mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.96,0:25:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你猜他們是用的什麼材料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what metal did they use to make the pipes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.13,0:25:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,修建他們大名鼎鼎的供水管道呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that carried the water through their legendary aqueducts?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.70,0:25:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,給你個提示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'll give you a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.70,0:25:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,水管這個詞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The word "plumbing" comes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.50,0:25:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,就是來源於拉丁文裏的 鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the Latin word for lead, "plumbum."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.31,0:25:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他們用什麼金屬製造他們的浴缸呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What metal did they use to line their famous baths?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.91,0:25:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果葡萄酒太酸時他們怎麼辦呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And how did they sweeten their wines when they were too sour?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的鍋碗瓢盆又是什麼材料呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What did they use to line their vats and cooking pots?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.45,0:26:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,部分歷史學家相信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are some historians who believe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.58,0:26:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛的廣泛使用是造成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the widespread use of lead was a major cause
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.95,0:26:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,羅馬帝國覆滅的主因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the decline and fall of the Roman Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼他們在知道鉛有毒後還繼續使用呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why did they continue to use lead long after they knew it was toxic?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它便宜 延展性好 製造簡單\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was cheap, very malleable, easy to work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.42,0:26:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,大量接觸致命劑量的那些人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the ones who were exposed to it at its most lethal levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.49,0:26:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,礦工和處理鉛的工人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the miners and workers who processed the lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.90,0:26:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,都是無關緊要的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were considered expendable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.93,0:26:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的性命不重要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their lives didn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.93,0:26:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是奴隸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.80,0:26:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上大部分的鉛最初都是深埋在地下 與生物保持安全的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the earth's lead started off at a safe distance from living things, down below the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.40,0:26:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但是大約8500年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but about 8,500 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.77,0:26:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,人們知道了如何從地裏挖東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}humans began figuring out how to dig into the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.91,0:26:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,從岩石中提煉金屬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and extract metals from rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.51,0:26:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,這個莊園新建成時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By the time this villa was new,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.67,0:26:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,也就幾千年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just a couple of thousand years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.97,0:26:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,羅馬人年產鉛8萬噸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the romans were producing 80,000 tons of lead a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.41,0:26:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼鉛對我們的危害這麼大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why is lead so poisonous to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.25,0:27:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,因為當鉛進入我們的體內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because when it gets into our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.92,0:27:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛假裝成其他金屬 比如鋅或者鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lead mimics other metals, like zinc and iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.62,0:27:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,細胞茁壯成長確實需要的元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ones our cells actually need to grow and flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.19,0:27:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,細胞中的酶被鉛的偽裝迷惑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Enzymes in the cell are fooled by the lead's masquerade,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.26,0:27:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,它們開始結合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they begin to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.59,0:27:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,這是致命的結合 因為鉛無法滿足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it's a dance of death, because the lead is an imposter
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.13,0:27:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,對細胞至關重要的需要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that can't fulfill the cell's vital needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.86,0:27:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛也會妨礙神經轉物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lead also blocks neurotransmitters,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.53,0:27:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,堵塞細胞間的交流網絡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the communication network between the cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.70,0:27:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,干擾對記憶和學習能力至關重要的分子的神經末梢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It interferes with the molecular receptors that are vital to memory and learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.30,0:27:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,對孩童尤為有害\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is especially damaging to children,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.27,0:27:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人可以避免\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but lead poisoning spares no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.84,0:27:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,從進入20世紀開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Starting at the turn of the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.21,0:27:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,含鉛油漆廠商們僱傭剛萌芽的廣告業者向消費者灌輸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the makers of leaded paint hired the fledgling advertising industry to persuade the consumer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.81,0:27:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛對孩童無害的觀念\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lead was child-friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.35,0:27:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,玩具小鉛兵對荷蘭小孩說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A little toy lead soldier once to the Dutch boy said,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.52,0:28:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我們好多小夥伴身體裏都有一點點的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"we have some fine relations who all contain some lead."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.52,0:28:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們開個派對讓你認識一下偉大的鉛家族中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Why don't you give a party so folks can meet and see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.05,0:28:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的快樂小夥伴吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"the other happy members of the great lead family?"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.45,0:28:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個到來的是快樂的電燈泡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first one at the party was gay electric light.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他說 "我非常亮"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"He said, " I'm very brilliant."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.12,0:28:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"我在黑夜裏閃閃發光"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"I always shine at night."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.96,0:28:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"我這麼亮可不是因為我的玻璃頭"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"No little of my brilliance is due to my glass head,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.03,0:28:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"讓光線更明亮"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which gives a light much brighter
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.56,0:28:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"其實是因為我是鉛做的"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"because it's made with lead."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.63,0:28:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,一對橡膠進來挽住荷蘭小孩的手臂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A pair or rubbers entered and took the Dutch boy's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.66,0:28:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他們說 "我們讓你的鞋子保持乾燥和暖和"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They said, " we are protectors who keep you dry and warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.37,0:28:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"製造我們的人說"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"You knew when we were molded, the man who made us said,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.30,0:28:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"我們堅固耐用還很活潑"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're strong and tough and lively
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"這是因為我們含有鉛"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"because in us, there's lead."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.47,0:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那時含鉛產品還沒有真正開始大發展\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But lead production didn't really shift into high gear
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.64,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,直到20年代早期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until the early 1920's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.87,0:28:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,化學狂人托馬斯·米基利夥同投資人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when chemist Thomas Midgley and inventor.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.87,0:28:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他也是氟利昂的發明人
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.85,0:29:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.24,0:28:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,通用汽車的查爾斯·凱特靈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Charles Kettering of General Motors
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.31,0:28:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,將四乙基鉛以抗爆劑為噱頭添加到汽油中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}found that tetraethyl lead could be marketed as an anti-knock additive to gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.31,0:28:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}四乙基鉛在那時用於提高汽油的辛烷值
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.68,0:28:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他們成立了乙基公司\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They formed a new company called the Ethyl Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.35,0:29:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,美國陸軍部曾經考慮用它做毒氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It had once been considered for use as a poison gas by the U.S. war department
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.59,0:29:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,和油漆中的鉛不同 四乙基鉛是脂溶性的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike the lead in paint, tetraethyl lead was fat soluble.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.42,0:29:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,皮膚接觸半杯的量就會致命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A half a cup of it on your skin could kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.56,0:29:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,生產廠家統計銷量可以達到每年6千萬噸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The manufacturers calculated that they could sell 60 million tons of it a year
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.66,0:29:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一個問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only problem was,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.93,0:29:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一些在特拉華州和新澤西州工廠工作的員工\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some of the workers who processed the stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.83,0:29:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,變得精神失常 出現幻覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in factories in Delaware and New Jersey were going insane, hallucinating,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.55,0:29:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,跳窗而出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}jumping out of windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.30,0:29:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,死狀恐怖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They died screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.34,0:29:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這時銷售宣傳需要的就不僅僅是會跳舞的燈泡了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was a selling job that would require a lot more than dancing light bulbs
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.41,0:29:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他們需要一個懂科學的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was needed was a man of science
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.55,0:29:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,安撫民眾的恐慌 並且提升鉛的形象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to calm the public's fears and improve lead's image.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.55,0:29:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他們找到了一個合適的人選\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They found the right man for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.68,0:29:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,那也是第一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was one of the first times
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.22,0:30:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,利用科學權威來遮掩對環境和公共健康的威脅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the authority of science was used to cloak a threat to public health and the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.42,0:30:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,辛辛那提的一位年輕博士 羅伯特基歐\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Robert Kehoe, a young doctor from Cincinnati,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.59,0:30:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,受雇於通用汽車\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was hired by GM.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.59,0:30:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他對公眾擔心的鉛的危害提出了反駁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He raised scientific doubts in the public mind about the dangers of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.30,0:30:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他說 鉛是環境中天然存在的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lead was naturally occurring in the environment, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.76,0:30:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,確實可能對第一線的工人造成職業傷害 但是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, there might be occupational hazards for the people who worked with lead, but
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.10,0:30:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,業界自我監管就夠了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that could be best handled by industry self-regulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.77,0:30:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,並沒有證據表明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And there was no evidence to suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.04,0:30:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛會對消費者構成威脅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lead posed any threat to the consumer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.27,0:30:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,幾十年來 沒有人反駁他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For decades no one challenged him...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.21,0:30:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,直到克萊爾·彼得森開始研究\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until Clair Patterson went searching
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.28,0:30:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的年齡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the age of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.59,0:30:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,克萊爾·彼得森對地球年齡的研究\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Claire Patterson's research on the age of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.09,0:30:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,使他成為世界上測量痕量鉛領域首屈一指的專家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had made him the world's leading expert on measuring trace amounts of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.22,0:30:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,和當時的其他人一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And like everyone else at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.16,0:30:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他猜想鉛是天然普遍存在的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he assumed the prevalence of lead occurred naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.39,0:31:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,像他這樣真正的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}True scientist that he was, he set out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.66,0:31:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他開始盡全力探究鉛是如何在環境中傳播的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to discover everything he could about how lead circulates through the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.30,0:31:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,依靠美國石油組織的撥款\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On a grant from the American Petroleum Institute,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.70,0:31:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他仔細的測量了深層和淺層海水中的鉛濃度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he carefully measured the concentrations of lead in deep and shallow seawater
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.70,0:31:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森又一次發現他的原始數據無法解釋了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once again, Patterson found that his initial data made no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.34,0:31:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,深層海水中只有極少量的鉛濃度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were only minuscule concentrations of lead in the deep ocean water
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.81,0:31:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但在淺水和水面上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in shallow waters and at the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.34,0:31:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛濃度卻要高出幾百倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the concentrations of lead were hundreds of times greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.08,0:31:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,海洋中 要用幾百年淺層海水才會與深層海水相混合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In any ocean, it takes a few hundred years for the shallow waters to mix with the deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.55,0:31:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森得出結論 表層海水中大量的鉛是最近才出現的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This told Patterson that the large amount of lead in the surface waters had arrived recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.75,0:31:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,否則它會分佈的更均勻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Otherwise it would have been more evenly distributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.72,0:31:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,知道了淺層的鉛濃度以及與深層混合所需要的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Knowing the quantity of lead in the shallow seas and the time needed to mix it into the deeper layers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.16,0:31:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他就可以估算出表面的鉛污染比率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he was able to estimate the rate of lead contamination at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.19,0:31:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森問自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson asked himself
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.06,0:32:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼能給全球的海洋帶來這麼多的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what could possibly supply lead to the world's oceans at such a rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.46,0:32:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,這些鉛都是哪裏來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where's all that lead coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.33,0:32:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道了 哈里森\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I think I know, Harrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.20,0:32:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,它來自含鉛汽油\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's from leaded gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.36,0:32:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 這個有點麻煩 派特\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, then we've got a problem, Pat,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.27,0:32:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們的資金都是從那裏來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because that's the same place the money comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.81,0:32:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,但是彼得森沒有屈服\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Patterson would not give in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.51,0:32:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他立即著手發表學術論文\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He went right to work on publishing the scientific paper
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.58,0:32:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,對含鉛汽油做出討伐\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that would make the case against leaded gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.51,0:32:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他把論文寄給了久負盛名的科學期刊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When he sent the paper to the prestigious scientific journal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.68,0:32:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,《自然》 彼得森將自己的名字放在後面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nature, Patterson put his own name second.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.68,0:32:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他過去常常這樣 幫助他的學生提高聲望\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He often did that with his students to advance their reputations
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.65,0:33:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他一輩子都在避免出風頭以及迴避隨之而來的好處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He made a lifelong point of shunning the limelight and the privileges that come with it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.19,0:33:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,發表後僅3天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only three days after publication...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.69,0:33:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,反擊開始了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the push-back began.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.65,0:33:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-你好 彼得森博士 -很高興見到你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- Hello, Dr. Patterson. - Pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.18,0:33:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,您的研究成果很了不起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Very impressed by your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.78,0:33:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,您的研究成果對我們石油化工行業有很大的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Your work is of great interest to us in the petroleum and chemical industries
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.69,0:33:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,多虧了你們的贊助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, it wouldn't have been possible without your funding.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.86,0:33:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,沒錯 我們還希望提供給你更多的幫助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Precisely. And there's so much more we'd like to do for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.86,0:33:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,正好 我還想在極地冰層中測量鉛含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, I've been thinking about measuring lead in polar ice
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.86,0:33:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,看看是不是和海洋中的結果一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to see if it shows the same kind of pattern as the oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛 你的工作已經結束了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lead? But you've already done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.03,0:33:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是時候研究其他微量元素了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're thinking it's time you move on to other trace elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.03,0:33:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,其實 彼得森博士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, Dr. Patterson,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.37,0:34:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有能力資助你去無限制地研究其他方面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our ability to fund you in any other line of research is...Virtually limitless.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.31,0:34:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛是一種神經毒素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Lead is a neurotoxin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.04,0:34:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你們將四乙基鉛從工廠運出來時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When you ship your tetraethyl lead from the factory...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.78,0:34:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在加進汽油之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before you add it to the gasoline...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.68,0:34:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是運送化學武器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's handled just like a chemical weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.68,0:34:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,都是有原因的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.15,0:34:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你們覺得這些鉛從排氣管中排出後都去了哪裏呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where do you suppose all that lead goes after it leaves the tailpipe
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.15,0:34:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,想想這會對我們和我們的後代造成什麼影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think about what it might be doing to us and our kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.27,0:34:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,基歐博士已經證明了這種程度的鉛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dr. Kehoe has shown that the level of lead in the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,在環境中就如同12月的雪一樣自然\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...is as natural as snow in December
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.96,0:34:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,那它怎麼會在深層海水中存在呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then why doesn't it show up in the deep water? Here,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.69,0:34:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我給你看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let me just show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.99,0:34:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,多謝了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Thanks for your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.46,0:34:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 你們還要把上百萬噸的毒氣排到我們呼吸的空氣中嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wait, you're just gonna keep on putting millions of tons of poison into the air we breathe?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.36,0:34:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,就算我的研究不能使你們停產 以後也有科學家可以做到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If my research doesn't put you out of business some future scientist will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.40,0:34:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,石油行業來的贊助一夜之間消失得無影無蹤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson's funding from the oil industry vanished overnight
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.54,0:34:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 他們要讓他失業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, they tried to get him fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.54,0:35:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但是美國政府 陸軍 海軍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the U.S. government... The Army, the Navy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.01,0:35:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,原子能委員會 公共衛生署\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the atomic energy commission, the public health service,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.51,0:35:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,還有國家科學基金會 都支持他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the National Science Foundation... Stood by him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.71,0:35:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,支持他的鉛污染研究\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}supporting his research on lead pollution.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.21,0:35:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,為了調查研究 從最北的格陵蘭到最南的大西洋都有他的足跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His investigations took him from Greenland in the far north to Antarctica in the far south
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.35,0:35:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,足跡遍佈各個河流與山川\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to rivers, mountains and valleys in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.89,0:35:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,即使面對最惡劣的條件\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In even the most hostile conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.92,0:35:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森和他的團隊協力複製了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson and his team worked to replicate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.49,0:35:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,無塵室的無污染環境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the immaculate environment of the clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.33,0:35:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他們每天都更換塑料制服\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their plastic suits were replaced daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.16,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在零下溫度下中工作10-12個小時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Working ten-to 12-hour days in subzero weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.00,0:35:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他們在南極洲冰層中鑽了深達200英尺的通道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they dug a 200-foot-long shaft into the ice of Antarctica
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.00,0:35:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}約為61米
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.70,0:35:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那是某種程度上的時間旅行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a form of time travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.70,0:35:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,取得了那是在工業革命開始前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to recover snow that had fallen three centuries ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.90,0:35:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,300年前的雪樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before the start of the Industrial Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.07,0:35:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你的鼻子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.87,0:35:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,快擦鼻子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wipe your nose, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.01,0:36:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你體內的鉛比冰裏的高1千倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a thousand times more lead in you than in this ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.54,0:36:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你這是想要污染整個樣本嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You want to contaminate the whole damn sample?!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.21,0:36:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,經過4個星期的精疲力盡的艱苦樣本採集工作後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After four grueling weeks of painstaking sample collection
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.12,0:36:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森準備回到實驗室了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson was ready to go back to the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.72,0:36:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,和海水中一樣 他發現在雪中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As with the oceans, he found that the amount of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.62,0:36:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百年前的鉛含量要低得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was much lower in the snow of a few hundred years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.42,0:36:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,不論在地球上的其他什麼地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No matter where he searched on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.72,0:36:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,也不管多久以前的樣本\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no matter how far he traveled back in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.56,0:36:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,結果都說明一件事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the results always told the same story:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.53,0:36:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,過去空氣和水中天然存在的含量要低得多得多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The naturally occurring levels in the air and water in the past, were far lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.60,0:36:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千年來 人們都知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For thousands of years, lead had been known
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.40,0:36:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛會造成腦損傷 影響發育\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to cause brain damage, developmental impairment,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.57,0:36:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,暴力行為 甚至致命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}violent behavior, and even death.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.11,0:36:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球年齡的研究中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In searching for the age of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.62,0:37:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森無意中發現了一場空前規模的毒害污染的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson had stumbled on the evidence for a mass poisoning on an unprecedented scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.02,0:37:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但是基歐和其他受雇於鉛工業的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Kehoe and the other scientists employed by the lead industry
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.76,0:37:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,勸說民眾無需為此擔心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}persuaded the public they had nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.13,0:37:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人都認為彼得森是個騙子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everyone thought Patterson was a crank
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.96,0:37:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,直到有個人開始關注這個問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until one man started to pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.03,0:37:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森將他的發現公佈於眾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson went public with his discoveries about lead in a big way
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.43,0:37:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他把研究結果發表在主要的環境健康期刊上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He published his findings in a major environmental health journal
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.77,0:37:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,也寄給了多位政府高層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and sent copies to various government leaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.10,0:37:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,包括一位很有影響力的參議員\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including one highly influential senator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.14,0:37:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,緬因州參議員埃德蒙·馬斯基\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Edmund Muskie of Maine
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.14,0:37:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.09,0:37:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,是時任的參議院大氣與水污染委員會主席\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was the chairman of the senate subcommittee on air and water pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.88,0:37:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,1966年他主持了關於鉛問題的聽證會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1966 he held hearings on the lead question.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.81,0:37:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,第一位證人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The first witness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.89,0:38:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,羅伯特基歐 含鉛汽油長期以來的支持者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was Dr. Robert Kehoe, longtime scientific advocate for leaded gasoline
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.76,0:38:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你的結論是不是 從1937年到現在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Is it, uh, your conclusion that, in 1937 to the present time, there has been
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.36,0:38:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,普通駕駛者和交警\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no increase in the amount of lead
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.82,0:38:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,還有加油站工作人員從大氣中吸入的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}taken in from the atmosphere by the average traffic policeman,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.69,0:38:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛的數量沒有增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}service station attendant, or... Or motorist?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.06,0:38:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,根本沒有證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is not the slightest evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.93,0:38:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,可以證明這段時間內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that there has been a change in this picture
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.63,0:38:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有任何改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}during this period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.63,0:38:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,完全沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.97,0:38:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,聽證會召開的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The hearings were scheduled to take place,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.88,0:38:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,特地選在彼得森在南極洲的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the fiercest critic, Claire Patterson was off in Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.71,0:38:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他出人意料地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But he unexpectedly appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.78,0:38:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在第五天出席了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the fifth day of testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.35,0:38:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去好像人體中鉛濃度的增加\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, looks like there seems to be an increase in the concentration of lead in people
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.55,0:38:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是與環境接觸的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a result of exposure to the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.99,0:38:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,是這樣嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.69,0:38:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.49,0:38:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,至於鑒定典型性德鉛含量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In identifying typical lead levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.16,0:38:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你用的是實地採集的測量結果嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you use actual measurements you've taken in the field?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.73,0:38:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.20,0:39:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這些檢測結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Are these observations different
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.73,0:39:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,與其他證人提出的有區別嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the ones we've been hearing about from other witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.20,0:39:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有 結果是相同的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, th... They're the same observations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.20,0:39:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你 你的證詞是說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You... You've testified that there has been
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.34,0:39:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,自然鉛含量沒有變化 是這樣嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no change in natural lead levels, is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.34,0:39:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.57,0:39:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你確定嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.31,0:39:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,非常肯定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.97,0:39:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,現在人體中的含量看似很尋常\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The levels we see in people today may be typical.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.84,0:39:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但絕不代表它們是天然的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they are not by any means natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.38,0:39:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你認同基歐博士的數據嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So you don't disagree with Dr. Kehoe's numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.05,0:39:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,認同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.55,0:39:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你是說 根據相同的數據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're saying that the same numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.51,0:39:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,得出了不同的結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are leading to different conclusions?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.05,0:39:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.52,0:39:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,這種話 通常是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You know, this is the kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.02,0:39:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,律師說的 不是科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we expect to hear from lawyers, not scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.99,0:39:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我也是這麼認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I would agree with that, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.72,0:39:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,基歐博士 你好像對你的結論很有把握\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You seem to be very sure of your conclusions, Dr. Kehoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.19,0:39:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我是目前在這個領域最有經驗的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It so happens that I have more experience in this field than anyone else alive
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.93,0:40:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,這種含量的鉛對人體有嚴重的長期傷害\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At these levels, lead is a severe chronic insult to the human body
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.33,0:40:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有醫學證據顯示 鉛會危害公眾健康\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is no medical evidence that lead has introduced a danger to public health.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.67,0:40:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,挖掘幾百萬噸有毒物質並將其\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's irresponsible to mine millions of tons
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.17,0:40:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,散佈到環境中 是極其不負責任的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of toxic material and disperse it into the environment!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.37,0:40:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,如果真的有證據 我們早就會發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If there was proof of harm, we would have found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.67,0:40:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你們以鉛牟利 當然不會將真實結果公諸於世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not if your purpose is to sell lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.08,0:40:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得森與整個行業又抗爭了20年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Patterson fought the industry for another 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.58,0:40:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,鉛才被禁止在美國消費品中使用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before lead was finally banned in U.S. consumer products.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.45,0:40:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這位找出地球年齡的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The man who figured out the age of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.92,0:40:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣也造就了20世紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was also responsible for one
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.92,0:40:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,最偉大的公眾健康問題的勝利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the greatest public health victories of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.75,0:40:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,短短幾年間 兒童平均\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In just a few years, average lead levels
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.96,0:40:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,血液鉛含量猛降百分之75\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the blood of children plummeted by some 75%.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.76,0:40:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如今 醫學界的共識是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Today, the medical consensus is unanimous...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.93,0:40:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,人體內的鉛含量不是無毒 只是量很少而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's no such thing as a nontoxic level of lead in humans, however small
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.26,0:40:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 科學家又發出了其他環境問題的警告\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Today, scientists sound the alarm on other environmental dangers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.10,0:41:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,既得利益團體依然僱傭他們自己的科學家以混淆視聽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vested interests still hire their own scientists to confuse the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.44,0:41:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但是到頭來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.37,0:41:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,最終的受害者 又是誰呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nature will not be fooled.
